{{More citations needed|date=September 2015}} [[File:PE-mapa-Canhotinho.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of Canhotinho within Pernambuco.]] '''Canhotinho''' (''Little Left-handed'') is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 223&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 24.381 inhabitants. [[File:2 arquivo.jpg|thumb|Canhotinho Flag]]
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Lajedo, Pernambuco|Lajedo]] and [[Jurema, Pernambuco|Jurema]] ('''N'''); [[Palmeirina]] ('''S'''); [[Quipapá]] and [[Alagoas]] state ('''E'''); [[Angelim]] and [[Calçado]] ('''W'''). * Area - 423.08&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 520 m * Hydrography - [[Mundaú River|Mundaú]] and [[Una River (Pernambuco)|Una rivers]] * Vegetation - [[Subperenifólia]] forest * Climate - Hot and humid * Annual average temperature - 21.7 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 223&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Canhotinho''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially [[sugarcane]], [[beans]], [[manioc]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]] and [[poultry]].
